    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Create_ActualExpenditureData",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to manage and process expenditure data within a budgeting system. It performs a series of operations to delete existing records for a specified billing period, reseed identity columns, and then insert and calculate budget and actual expenditure data. The procedure is structured to handle data insertion, summarization, and calculation in a step-by-step manner, utilizing additional stored procedures for specific tasks."
        }
